The paper deals with the use of mobile phone data to extract socio-economic indicators, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of data mining and machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.SD). The paper also deals with the measurement of community socio-economic status, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SOC) and computational economics (cs.CE).
